org.sat4j.tools

インタフェース SolutionFoundListener

  • 既知のサブインタフェースのリスト:
    ILauncherMode
    既知の実装クラスのリスト:
    AbstractLexicoHelper, CheckMUSSolutionListener, LexicoHelper, LeximinHelper, LinMultiObjHelper, SteppedTimeoutLexicoHelper

    public interface SolutionFoundListener
    Allows the end user to react when a new solution is found. This is typically the case when doing some upper bound optimization, or iterating on the models, or computing all MUses.
    導入されたバージョン:
    2.3.3

    • メソッドの詳細

      • onSolutionFound

        void onSolutionFound(int[] solution)
        Callback method called when a new solution is found. While a solution will often be a model, it might also be the case that the solution is something else (MUS, group MUS, etc).
        パラメータ:
        solution - a set of Dimacs literals.

      • onSolutionFound

        void onSolutionFound(IVecInt solution)
        Callback method called when a new solution is found. While a solution will often be a model, it might also be the case that the solution is something else (MUS, group MUS, etc).
        パラメータ:
        solution - a set of Dimacs literals.

      • onUnsatTermination

        void onUnsatTermination()
        Callback method called when the search is finished (either unsat problem or no more solutions found)
